headlines.description: — For the second straight game, the Hornets saved their best for last.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges scores 30 points, Hornets beat careless Cavs 123-112

events.name: New York Knicks at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — As Tom Thibodeau headed in for his postgame news conference following the New York Knicks’ 121-96 rout of the Orlando Magic on Friday night, a fan implored the notoriously grumpy head coach to “be happy.”
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks make 24 3s, cruise past rebuilding Magic 121-96

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal's absence put Spencer Dinwiddie and Kyle Kuzma on the spot — and those two made quite a first impression on their new fans in Washington.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dinwiddie leads Wizards to 135-134 OT win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Ben Simmons wasn't there. Joel Embiid conceded he should not have played. With Philadelphia's All-Star cornerstones absent or injured, Kevin Durant and Brooklyn had the opening they needed to spoil the 76ers' opener with a rally down the stretch.
— Raptors coach Nick Nurse didn't think Scottie Barnes played that badly in his first NBA game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors beat Celtics 115-83, spoil Udoka's home opener

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine needed some time to get going. Once he did, there was no stopping him.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 32, DeRozan 26 as Bulls pound Pelicans 128-112

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Christian Wood had 31 points and 14 rebounds and Houston beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 124-91 on Friday night in the Rockets’ home opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wood helps Rockets rout Thunder 124-91 in home opener

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Not everyone thought Nikola Jokic should have won the MVP award last season. His Denver teammates did, and one, in fact, predicted he would repeat.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic posts 32 points, 16 boards; Nuggets top Spurs 102-96

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Dwight Howard and Anthony Davis both say their physical confrontation on the Los Angeles Lakers' bench was a momentary disagreement that has already been resolved.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dwight, AD downplay confrontation in Lakers' loss to Suns

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 27 points, Rudy Gobert had 17 points and 20 rebounds, and the Utah Jazz beat the Sacramento Kings 110-101 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 27, Gobert leads late surge, Jazz beat Kings
